See the file doc/api/coding-style.qdoc for our coding standard.

For instructions on how to set up the Qt Hldplugin repository to contribute
patches back to Qt Hldplugin, please check:

https://wiki.qt.io/Setting_up_Gerrit#How_to_get_started_-_Gerrit_registration

Qt Hldplugin has integrated auto tests, and further external tests in the
subdirectory 'tests'.

To build the integrated auto tests, build Qt Hldplugin with the additional
QMake option TEST=1

To build also the auto tests, manual tests and unit tests in the 'tests'
subdirectory, use the QMake option BUILD_TESTS=1

Afterwards:

* The tests from the 'tests' subdirectory can be run as individual applications.
  They are also available as separate Run configuration from within Qt Hldplugin.

* All the integrated tests for a specific plugin can be run with:

 qthldplugin -test QtSupport

* To run only a specific test case, use:

 qthldplugin -test QtSupport,testQtOutputFormatter

Note: Adding -test to Qt Hldplugin will run the tests in a clean settingspath.
To run them with specific settings, -settingspath /path has to be provided.
